        "timestamp": "2019-09-05 19:45:04.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nShould not have merged, the job fails:   ERROR: InterpreterNotFound: python3.7\n\nThe challenge: which builder image has python3.7?  Apparently ubuntu1604-builder-4c-4g does not, but possibly ubuntu1604-docker-8c-8g *does*.  I will try that in the Jenkins sandbox.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "6330766ed551cc3776ab26b95b5a9ac55ff840f3",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 105,
          "name": "Tony Hansen",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "tony@att.com",
          "username": "TonyLHansen"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-06 14:30:56.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\ncan you use python3.6?\nI think the servers have 3.6 available",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "86091cc31770ecb8c9847646e7614cf69021e697",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 515,
          "name": "Tommy Carpenter",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": null,
          "username": "tommycarpenter"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-06 14:37:54.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nno this whole effort was in attempt to get away from that. The unit tests now try to run in both. \n\ntox runs in 37 successfully during the verify jobs. The verify jobs use the python jjb which has 37 fine. The problem is there is some difference between the python jjb and the tox sonar job. we are investigating. \n\nbut backtracking to 36 is definitely not the way.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "c6893c8bfecd231d9ab4e6cf8b235842afeeab99",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 515,
          "name": "Tommy Carpenter",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": null,
          "username": "tommycarpenter"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-06 14:46:26.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI think we may know the issue. We aren't specifying the python version correctly in the sonar job",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "06bd5b667b40304b0e127efeb59e5661aa7b84a6",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 515,
          "name": "Tommy Carpenter",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": null,
          "username": "tommycarpenter"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-06 15:16:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nwe may have found the issue; or at least we were able to get a similar repo working in the sandbox that had the same error.\n\nthere needs to be a patch to `tox-install.sh` in the LF; tox-install currently installs tox using `python`, which points to python2, but then we are running tox against a py3 repo.\n\nwe made a ticket: https://jira.linuxfoundation.org/browse/RELENG-2361\n\nwe are going to try the same step in the sandbox for the CBS and report back",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "9342c1c800a11406ed768b8dbd95682fd7f532e2",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 515,
          "name": "Tommy Carpenter",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": null,
          "username": "tommycarpenter"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-06 15:31:09.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nwe now have this successfully working in the sandbox: https://jenkins.onap.org/sandbox/job/dcaegen2-platform-configbinding-tox-sonar/8/console\nthis works after having changed tox to be installed using python3\n\n\nthere is still a big question. Why does the VERIFY work on the CBS, but the SONAR does not work, given that they both use tox-install? There is still some difference between the two jjb jobs that we have not identified.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "5cafbe7e4ed90896e449470d1848aea9fd56a5b4",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 515,
          "name": "Tommy Carpenter",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": null,
          "username": "tommycarpenter"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-06 15:53:34.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nwe have answered this question.\n\nthe current verify job for the CBS does not actually work.\n\nhowever, BOTH sonar and the verify job work when we make the change to tox_install.sh. As do ORAN projects.\n\nSo, this ticket is the key to all of the issues: https://jenkins.onap.org/sandbox/job/dcaegen2-platform-configbinding-tox-sonar/8/console",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
